question: What are the anatomical entities including cell types, if any, where the human gene APOC1 is expressed at the post-juvenile stage along with its expression score independently of the strain and sex? Provide also the taxon scientific name and the taxon common name and the gene identifier.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?cellType ?expressioncondition ?organism ?taxon ?gene_identifier ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?cellTypeName ?efo_0000399 ?score ?expression ?taxon_scientificname ?gene ?taxon_commonname WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?expression a genex:Expression .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionCondition ?expressioncondition .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .
	?expression genex:hasSequenceUnit ?gene .
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?cellType .
	?cellType rdfs:label ?cellTypeName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?efo_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 rdf:type efo:EFO_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 rdfs:label "post-juvenile" .
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:commonName "human" .
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/scientificName> ?taxon_scientificname.
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/commonName> ?taxon_commonname.
	?gene <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> ?gene_identifier.
	FILTER(       ?anatomicalentity !=  obo:GO_0005575       )
	FILTER(       ?anatomicalentity != ?cellType       )
}

PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX efo: <http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?expressioncondition ?efo_0000399_label ?strain ?anatomicalentity_label ?anatomicalentity_description ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?efo_0000399 ?efo_0000399_description ?gene_description ?gene WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?expressioncondition.
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity obo:GO_0005575 .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?efo_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 a efo:EFO_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 rdfs:label "life cycle" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?strain .
	?strain rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?efo_0000399 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0000399_label.
	?efo_0000399 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?efo_0000399_description.
	?anatomicalentity <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?anatomicalentity_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?anatomicalentity_description.
	?gene <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?gene_description.
}

question: What are the anatomical entities where the P02654 gene is expressed? Note that P02654 is a UniProtKB identifier of the APOC1 human gene. Provide also the anatomical entity label and the anatomical entity description and the gene description.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up-protein:<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?anatomicalentity_label ?anatomicalentity_description ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?gene_description ?gene WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity .
	?gene lscr:xrefUniprot up-protein:P02654 .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?anatomicalentity <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?anatomicalentity_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?anatomicalentity_description.
	?gene <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?gene_description.
}

question: What are the anatomical entities where the APOC1 Homo sapiens gene is expressed? Provide also the gene see also.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?organism ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?gene ?gene_seealso WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	### Specifying species:
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:scientificName "Homo sapiens" .
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?gene_seealso.
}

question: What are the anatomical entities including cell types, if any, where the human gene APOC1 is expressed at the post-juvenile stage along with its expression score independently of the strain and sex? Provide also the taxon scientific name and the taxon common name and the strain label and the anatomical entity label and the anatomical entity description and the gene expression has expression level score and the gene expression has false discovery rate p-value and the gene identifier.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?cellType ?expression ?score ?expressioncondition ?gene_identifier ?anatomicalentity_description ?taxon_scientificname ?efo_0005135_label ?expression_hasfalsediscoveryratep_value ?organism ?anatomicalentity_label ?expression_hasexpressionlevelscore ?stage ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?cellTypeName ?efo_0005135 ?gene ?taxon_commonname WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?expression a genex:Expression .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionCondition ?expressioncondition .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .
	?expression genex:hasSequenceUnit ?gene .
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?cellType .
	?cellType rdfs:label ?cellTypeName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?stage .
	?stage rdfs:label "post-juvenile" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?efo_0005135 .
	?efo_0005135 a efo:EFO_0005135.
	?efo_0005135 rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:commonName "human" .
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/scientificName> ?taxon_scientificname.
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/commonName> ?taxon_commonname.
	?efo_0005135 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0005135_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?anatomicalentity_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?anatomicalentity_description.
	?expression <http://purl.org/genex#hasExpressionLevel> ?expression_hasexpressionlevelscore.
	?expression <http://purl.org/genex#hasFDRpvalue> ?expression_hasfalsediscoveryratep_value.
	?gene <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> ?gene_identifier.
	FILTER(                 ?anatomicalentity != obo:GO_0005575                 )
	FILTER(                 ?anatomicalentity != ?cellType                 )
}

PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX efo: <http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?expressioncondition ?efo_0000399_label ?strain ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?efo_0000399 ?efo_0000399_description ?gene ?gene_label WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?expressioncondition.
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity obo:GO_0005575 .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?efo_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 a efo:EFO_0000399 .
	?efo_0000399 rdfs:label "life cycle" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?strain .
	?strain rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?efo_0000399 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0000399_label.
	?efo_0000399 <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?efo_0000399_description.
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?gene_label.
}

question: What are the anatomical entities including cell types, if any, where the human gene APOC1 is expressed at the post-juvenile stage along with its expression score independently of the strain and sex? Provide also the strain label.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?cellType ?expressioncondition ?organism ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?cellTypeName ?expression ?score ?efo_0005135 ?efo_0005135_label ?stage ?gene WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?expression a genex:Expression .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionCondition ?expressioncondition .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .
	?expression genex:hasSequenceUnit ?gene .
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?cellType .
	?cellType rdfs:label ?cellTypeName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?stage .
	?stage rdfs:label "post-juvenile" .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?efo_0005135 .
	?efo_0005135 a efo:EFO_0005135.
	?efo_0005135 rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:commonName "human" .
	?efo_0005135 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0005135_label.
	FILTER(   ?anatomicalentity != obo:GO_0005575   )
	FILTER(   ?anatomicalentity != ?cellType   )
}

PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX up-taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?expressioncondition ?stageIRI ?anatName ?score ?efo_0005135 ?efo_0005135_label ?anat ?expression ?gene ?gene_label WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?expression a genex:Expression .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionCondition ?expressioncondition .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .
	?expression genex:hasSequenceUnit ?gene .
	?gene dcterms:identifier "118230125" .
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anat .
	?anat rdfs:label ?anatName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage ?stageIRI .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?efo_0005135 .
	?efo_0005135 a efo:EFO_0005135.
	?efo_0005135 rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?efo_0005135 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0005135_label.
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?gene_label.
	FILTER(     ?anat !=  obo:GO_0005575     )
}

question: What are the anatomical entities where the P02654 gene is expressed? Note that P02654 is a UniProtKB identifier of the APOC1 human gene. Provide also the gene see also.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up-protein:<http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?gene ?gene_seealso ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity .
	?gene lscr:xrefUniprot up-protein:P02654 .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?gene_seealso.
}

PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX up-taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX ensembl: <http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/resource/ensembl/>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?expressioncondition ?anatomicalentity_label ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?expression ?score ?efo_0005135 ?efo_0005135_label ?gene WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?expression a genex:Expression .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionCondition ?expressioncondition .
	?expression genex:hasExpressionLevel ?score .
	?expression genex:hasSequenceUnit ?gene .
	?gene lscr:xrefEnsemblGene ensembl:ENSG00000130208 .
	?expressioncondition a genex:ExpressionCondition.
	?expressioncondition genex:hasAnatomicalEntity ?anatomicalentity .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity.
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasDevelopmentalStage obo:UBERON_0000113 .
	?expressioncondition genex:hasSex "any".
	?expressioncondition genex:hasStrain ?efo_0005135 .
	?efo_0005135 a efo:EFO_0005135.
	?efo_0005135 rdfs:label "wild-type" .
	?efo_0005135 <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?efo_0005135_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?anatomicalentity_label.
	FILTER(     ?anatomicalentity !=  obo:GO_0005575     )
}

question: What are the anatomical entities where the APOC1 Homo sapiens gene is expressed? Provide also the taxon scientific name and the taxon common name and the anatomical entity label and the anatomical entity description and the gene see also.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?organism ?taxon ?anatomicalentity_label ?anatomicalentity_description ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?taxon_scientificname ?gene ?gene_seealso ?taxon_commonname WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	### Specifying species:
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:scientificName "Homo sapiens" .
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/scientificName> ?taxon_scientificname.
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/commonName> ?taxon_commonname.
	?anatomicalentity <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> ?anatomicalentity_label.
	?anatomicalentity <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> ?anatomicalentity_description.
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?gene_seealso.
}

question: What is all the metadata related to the ENSG00000130208 gene, where ENSG00000130208 is the identifier of the APOC1 human gene.  Provide also the gene see also and the gene identifier.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?organism ?ncbi ?gene_identifier ?symbol ?description ?id ?ensembl ?gene ?gene_seealso ?uniprot ?links WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene rdfs:label ?symbol .
	?gene rdfs:seeAlso ?links .
	?gene dcterms:description ?description .
	?gene dcterms:identifier ?id .
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?gene <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?gene_seealso.
	?gene <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> ?gene_identifier.
	OPTIONAL { ?gene lscr:xrefUniprot ?uniprot . } 
	OPTIONAL { ?gene lscr:xrefEnsemblGene ?ensembl . } 
	OPTIONAL { ?gene lscr:xrefNCBIGene ?ncbi . } 
	FILTER(     ?id = "ENSG00000130208"     )
}

	FILTER(       ?anatomicalentity != ?cellType       )
}

question: What are the anatomical entities where the APOC1 Homo sapiens gene is expressed? Provide also the taxon scientific name.
sparql:
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?organism ?taxon ?anatomicalentity ?anatomicalentityName ?taxon_scientificname ?gene WHERE { 
	?gene a orth:Gene .
	?gene genex:isExpressedIn ?anatomicalentity.
	?gene rdfs:label "APOC1" .
	?anatomicalentity a genex:AnatomicalEntity .
	?anatomicalentity rdfs:label ?anatomicalentityName .
	### Specifying species:
	?gene orth:organism ?organism .
	?organism obo:RO_0002162  ?taxon .
	?taxon a up:Taxon .
	?taxon up:scientificName "Homo sapiens" .
	?taxon <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/scientificName> ?taxon_scientificname.
}
